            <fr:title text="Dimension of a Finite Vector Space">Dimension of a Finite Vector Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The dimension of a <fr:link href="/forest/0017/" title="Finite Dimensional Vector Space" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/0017/" display-uri="0017" type="local">finite dimensional vector space</fr:link> is the length of any <fr:link href="/forest/001D/" title="Finite Dimensional Basis" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/001D/" display-uri="001D" type="local">basis</fr:link> of the vector space. Important to this definition is the fact that every basis of a given space has the same length.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
